er, likely confused with Sally Brooks who was the biological mother).","gender":"female","display_name":"Laura Electa Hooker Shader","bio_blurb":"Vermont-born Hooker daughter who lived to ninety-three"},"birth":{"year":1818,"state":"Vermont","country":"United States","historical_notes":"Per WikiTree: b.1818 Vermont — making her older than her EH-listed siblings Myron Smith (1820) and Thomas Cullen (1822). Likely Myron Hooker + Sally Brooks first child; EH 1272 omitted her, possibly because she had no Hooker-surname descendants to track."},"death":{"year":1911,"month":11,"day":7,"city":"Shelton","county":"Fairfield County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H01272","mother_id":"X02278","father_research_notes":"Myron Hooker (H01272)","mother_research_notes":"Per Findagrave: Betsey Bacon Hooker (X02278). EARLIER hypothesis was Sally Brooks (X02277) based on timing logic (Laura b.1818, Sally Brooks's children Myron Smith b.1820 and Thomas Cullen b.1822). Findagrave likely correct that Betsey is the BIOLOGICAL mother — meaning Betsey may have been Myron's first wife, OR Laura was Betsey's daughter from her earlier Bacon marriage who took Hooker surname after her mother remarried Myron. EH 1272 omitted Laura entirely. UNRESOLVED — going with Findagrave per primary memorial source."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02280","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["X02269","HD3269","HD3274"]}],"tags":["extraordinary_longevity","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"WikiTree: Laura E. (Hooker) Shader","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Casteel-170"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"She buried the genealogist’s mistake by outliving everyone","body":"Born in frontier Vermont in 1818, she lived to ninety-three — long enough to see the railroad, the telegraph, the Civil War, and electric light reach the country towns of her girlhood. One of her daughters, Violetta, raised thirteen children of her own."}],"cross_connections":[{"related_person_id":"H02424","relationship":"first_cousin_cousin_marriage_convergence","evidence":"Laura's father Myron Hooker and Thomas Edwin's father Thomas Gould were half-brothers via Capt. Thomas Hooker (H00491). Two of Thomas Edwin's sons (Thomas Harvey + William Henry) each married into Laura's line — closing two cousin loops.","display_label":"Two of his sons married into her descendants","type":"family_connection"},{"type":"cousin_marriage","related_id":"H02424","display_label":"His son Thomas Harvey Hooker married her daughter Caroline Shader","notes":"Cousin marriage documentation. HD3260 (Laura Electa Hooker Shader) and H02424 (Thomas Edwin Hooker) are niece and uncle — Laura's father Myron Hooker (H01272) was Thomas Edwin's half-brother. Their respective children X02269 Caroline E. Shader (Laura's daughter) and H03872 Thomas Harvey Hooker (Thomas Edwin's son) were third cousins who married Feb 12, 1863."}],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport Monroe County NY — Section 2 Lot 56 (unmarked grave)"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"laura-shader-1818"},"X02269":{"id":"X02269","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Caroline","middle_name":"E.","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Shader","married_names":["Hooker"],"nickname":"Carrie","gender":"female","display_name":"Caroline E. \"Carrie\" Shader Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1842,"month":3,"day":16,"city":"Wethersfield","county":"Wyoming County",