in a single household. Lydia descended from Captain Thomas Hooker through her grandmother Laura Electa Hooker Shader (Myron Hooker's daughter); William Henry descended through the parallel Thomas Edwin Hooker branch. They were third cousins once removed, and their three children inherited double Hooker ancestry."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three children, daughter Ethel died age thirty-one","body":"Lydia and William Henry had three children: Charles Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at thirty-one), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993). The Hooker-Zastrow line traces forward through Ethel; the Hebner-Cook-Stafford family that descended from these children is doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1865, died Holley 1915","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson was born July 9 or 10, 1865 in Murray, Orleans County New York. She died February 8, 1915 in Holley, Orleans County New York at age forty-nine — predeceasing her husband William Henry by eighteen years. The Orleans County NY core of the Hooker-Shader-Robinson cousin network spanned three generations of intermarriages within the same upstate New York county."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lydia-hooker-1865"},"HD3271":{"id":"HD3271","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":10},"bio":{"first_name":"Shader","middle_name":"William","last_name":"Robinson","married_names":[],"extra_names":"Named after his grandfather William Henry Shader","gender":"male"